Durban - Two men in their 30s were killed when the car they were travelling in crashed into a barrier and steel structure on the M4 northbound at the Quality Street off-ramp in Durban early on Sunday morning, KwaZulu-Natal paramedics said.Just after 1.30am Rescue Care paramedics responded to the scene to find both the driver and passenger were severely trapped in the wreckage, spokesman Garrith Jamieson said.&#x201C;Both patients were assessed. However, they had sustained fatal injuries and there was nothing more paramedics could do. They were both declared deceased on the scene. Durban fire department had to use the jaws-of-life to free the two from the wreckage.&#x201D;The cause of the crash was unknown, but police were investigating the accident, he said. African News Agency